Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,DETECTIVE CONAN EPISODE 1066 \N"'Til Death Do Us Part"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.39,0:00:08.94,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.50,0:00:15.78,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,That was a cute incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:18.79,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,but let's pull ourselves together \Nand proceed with the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:23.04,Shinpo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,1)}Yokoyama Shinpo (28) \NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.70,0:00:31.46,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:33.42,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for the bride \Nto make her appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.18,0:00:41.02,Sayoko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,375)}Imamura Sayoko (24) \NHousekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:08.25,DCMain,SAYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.06,0:01:10.02,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.02,0:01:10.88,DCMain,SHINPO,0000,0000,0000,,Sayoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:23.86,DCMain,SHINPO,0000,0000,0000,,Sayoko! Sayoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.86,0:01:25.34,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Shinpo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.34,0:01:26.75,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, call an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:27.35,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.38,0:01:31.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. She's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.28,0:01:33.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The time is 13:22.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:35.78,DCMain,SHINPO,0000,0000,0000,,Sayoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.92,0:01:38.36,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:40.74,Hiroko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,375)}Nagashima Hiroko (23) \NWedding Planner
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.36,0:01:41.06,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why did she have to die now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.87,0:01:45.33,Priest,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,375)}Kawasu Alex Harutoshi (58) \NPriest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.16,0:01:45.50,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's too soon. She's too young.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:48.16,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.83,0:01:51.88,Yamada,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,1)}Yamada Gakuto (27) \NOfficer Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.77,0:01:51.51,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}In that case, me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.14,0:01:54.15,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They got what they deserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.21,0:01:55.71,Naho,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,375)}Mizuguchi Naho (23) \NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:56.13,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If anything, this should've happened sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:59.20,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,If only I'd noticed sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.26,0:02:03.51,Nobuteru,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,1)}Yokoyama Nobuteru (57) \NExecutive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:03.51,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I knew it. This marriage was cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.70,0:02:08.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious clouds block your field of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.60,0:02:10.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Clear them away with deductive \Nreasoning and the sky sparkles!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.36,0:02:12.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,During the highlight of a happy day,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:14.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,why did their vows disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:15.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:17.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:20.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:07.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,1)}'Til Death Do Us Part
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:05.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"'Til Death Do Us Part!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.02,0:04:17.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So, how did you end up at the \Nscene of the murder this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.73,0:04:22.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I met the groom's father at a bar I frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:27.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He ended up inviting you to the wedding \Nbecause you were having so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:29.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And yet another incident \Noccurred at the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.94,0:04:32.44,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Something always seems \Nto happen around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.44,0:04:34.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.60,0:04:37.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see any obvious injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:41.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Imamura \NSayoko-san, 24 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:43.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,She was a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:49.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As you all witnessed, her time \Nof death was 13:22 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.54,0:04:53.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to forensics, the \Ncause of death is poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.20,0:04:56.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of poison was the bride given?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.33,0:05:00.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Matter from poisonous mushrooms \Nwere found inside her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.20,0:05:06.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Ingesting even a small amount paralyzes your \Nentire body and causes death within an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:09.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,An hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.31,0:05:16.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then anyone who gave her something \Nto eat or drink is a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.88,WaitingRoom,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Wedding Party Waiting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:19.88,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,This is Nagashima Hiroko-san, \Nthe wedding planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:23.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You apparently gave \NImamura-san water to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.88,0:05:27.28,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Supporting the bride is my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.28,0:05:29.64,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Making her drink water is part of my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:34.88,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I stuck a straw in a bottle so \Nher makeup wouldn't be ruined
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.88,0:05:36.89,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,and had her take frequent sips of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:41.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We heard a lot of demands were made of \Nyou while preparing for this wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.16,0:05:45.53,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit they were such difficult \Nclients I wanted to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:50.33,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,They planned their schedule down to the \Nminute and kept trying to squeeze in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:53.29,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at this. There isn't \Neven room to take a breather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.29,0:05:55.29,Schedule,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,13:25 Bride's Entrance \N13:30 Scripture Reading \N13:40 Vows Exchanged \N13:45 Kiss \N13:50 Ring Dog's Entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.57,0:06:00.41,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,The day after criticizing the planned \Nreception and changing the color of the napkins,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:02.80,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was told to change it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:06.20,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Being self-centered came naturally to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:08.88,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,When you said you wanted to kill her...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:11.14,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:16.02,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,That would ruin the wedding \Nceremony I put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.09,0:06:20.06,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Although, ultimately, it was ruined anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:25.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said, "Why now?" What \Ndid you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.09,0:06:29.83,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,A spectacular fireworks display was \Nplanned for after the bride's entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:32.32,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Getting that authorized was a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:37.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, whose dog was it \Nthat interrupted the ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.16,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,That was Yokoyama-san's dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.16,0:06:41.53,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was supposed to be the ring dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.53,0:06:42.75,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Ring dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.09,0:06:45.20,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,They carry the wedding rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.20,0:06:48.73,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,These days some couples have a dog do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.34,0:06:53.26,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have business with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:55.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yamada Gakuto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.20,0:06:57.56,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a friend of the groom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.56,0:06:59.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They work at the same company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:03.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You went to the bride's room \Njust before the ceremony began.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:05.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.33,0:07:10.52,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm both the groom's friend \Nand Sayoko's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.02,0:07:14.53,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I went to congratulate her personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:17.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you give her anything to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.74,0:07:19.46,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:22.54,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,But I did give her something to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.37,0:07:24.44,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,From this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:26.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's liquor, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.56,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I always carry this with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.56,0:07:32.71,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,She asked for a drink to pick her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.89,0:07:37.62,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Could we examine that flask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.62,0:07:39.22,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.70,0:07:41.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:46.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the bride collapsed, \Nyou said, "Perfect."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.34,0:07:48.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:50.28,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,You were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:52.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:56.56,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something we should \Ndiscuss in front of children,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:07:58.04,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,but Sayoko and I were...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.40,0:08:02.85,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, my pen ran out of ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.85,0:08:05.54,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you borrow one from \Nsomeone in the hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.73,0:08:08.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure. I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:12.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh... Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.26,0:08:14.33,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.33,0:08:20.43,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell Shinpo, but she and I were dating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.80,0:08:23.58,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew she was getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.58,0:08:25.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So she was two-timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:27.98,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,She's the two-timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.98,0:08:31.82,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I said it was perfect because \Nnow that she was gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.82,0:08:34.87,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I was free to find a new love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.64,0:08:38.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this guy for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.34,0:08:44.16,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yokoyama Nobuteru-san, \Nthe groom's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,My deepest sympathies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:51.16,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable. How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.16,0:08:55.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Before the ceremony, you \Nwent to the bride's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:08:56.18,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:08:59.81,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I heard her parents weren't around,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:03.36,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I could be there \Nfor her in place of her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.84,0:09:07.75,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she loved chocolate, \Nso I brought her some.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.38,0:09:11.87,DCFlashback,SAYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could eat them \Nnow, but I put my nails on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.87,0:09:13.65,DCFlashback,SAYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you feed me, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:15.17,DCFlashback,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.17,0:09:18.26,DCFlashback,SAYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. We're father and daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.26,0:09:20.46,DCFlashback,SAYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.84,0:09:25.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Her cause of death was poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.91,0:09:26.99,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.99,0:09:29.66,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't poison the chocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.66,0:09:32.38,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We're still just talking to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:33.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:36.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.50,0:09:40.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said, "If only I noticed sooner."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.12,0:09:44.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"I knew it. This marriage was cursed."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.55,0:09:46.06,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,You were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:51.36,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I actually hired a detective \Nto conduct an investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.36,0:09:54.82,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,and the results weren't very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.16,0:09:56.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.70,0:10:01.97,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,Sayoko-san had quite a history \Nwith men since she was in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:07.86,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I told my son about it, \Nbut he wouldn't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.86,0:10:10.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They say love is blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.51,0:10:15.46,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.64,0:10:19.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san, when the bride collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.47,0:10:23.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,you said, "They got what they deserved. \NThis should've happened sooner."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:26.97,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,Sayoko and I had been friends since school,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.97,0:10:30.68,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,but she'd been jumping from one \Nman to the next since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.68,0:10:34.78,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,I said that because I knew something \Nterrible would happen to her eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.41,0:10:38.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Can you think of anyone who may \Nhave held a grudge against her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:40.98,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many, I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:42.02,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.05,0:10:52.74,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the groom's father feeding \Nchocolate to the bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:57.55,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,The door happened to be open when \NI passed by the bride's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:11:00.43,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I saw what was going on inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.49,0:11:03.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What time did you see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:06.90,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was around 12:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.90,0:11:11.18,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagashima-san last had \Nher drink water at 12:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.18,0:11:14.81,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But since she was frequently hydrating,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.30,0:11:17.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,it'll be difficult to determine \Nexactly when that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.17,0:11:23.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,She drank Yamada-san's liquor around 12:20.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.39,0:11:25.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you said the poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.34,0:11:30.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to forensics, the poison comes \Ninto effect within an hour and kills the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:34.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was the liquor that she \Ndrank an hour earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:40.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible, but Yamada-san \Nwillingly handed over his flask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.26,0:11:44.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:44.91,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:48.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said something when the bride collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:50.84,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I meant exactly what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.84,0:11:55.66,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,She was too young to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.66,0:11:57.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:01.67,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I've uploaded the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.17,0:12:07.24,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-san, we have the \Nresults from forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.45,0:12:08.74,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:11.65,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They found nothing in the \Nplastic bottle and flask.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:15.46,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But mushroom poison was \Nfound in the chocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.46,0:12:16.67,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.85,0:12:21.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you give the bride chocolates?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:23.14,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.96,0:12:30.59,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,because Sayoko-san said she loved Mativa \Nchocolates during the wedding rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.28,0:12:35.44,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I bought chocolates at a department \Nstore and gave them to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:38.74,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Why was there poison in chocolates \Nyou bought from a department store?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.74,0:12:41.38,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:43.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Does this settle it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.13,0:12:45.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:46.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:53.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Would he really poison the chocolates he \Ngave her when he knew he'd be suspected?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.24,0:12:59.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If the groom's father was \Nagainst the marriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:01.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he would've found another way to oppose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:05.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we'll have to keep investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:09.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This was the act of someone who \Nhad a grudge against the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:11.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.77,WaitingRoom,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Wedding Party Waiting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:19.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the bride's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.32,0:13:28.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Left of the bride's room is an elevator hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:32.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Past that is the guest waiting room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.08,0:13:32.74,WaitingRoom,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Guest Waiting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.48,0:13:34.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:41.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Poor dog. You're all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.31,0:13:45.01,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.78,0:13:47.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The leash has been cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.56,0:13:51.01,WaitingRoom,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(955,1)}Wedding Party Waiting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:50.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.22,0:13:52.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:54.27,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:58.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can I see your ceremony schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.77,0:14:00.57,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:02.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:04.28,Schedule,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,13:25 Bride's Entrance \N13:30 Scripture Reading \N13:40 Vows Exchanged \N13:45 Kiss \N13:50 Ring Dog's Entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.77,0:14:03.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.45,0:14:06.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.17,0:14:11.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony started at a different time \Nfrom what's listed on this schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.13,0:14:12.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:13.90,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.90,0:14:17.43,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,One of the groom's shoes went \Nmissing right before the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.43,0:14:19.45,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was ultimately found in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.45,0:14:22.04,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,but it delayed the start by five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:23.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:24.37,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not much of a reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.37,0:14:28.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were ready by early this morning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:30.84,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I got here at six this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.84,0:14:34.28,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I had so much to do, I had \Nno idea what was going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.68,0:14:38.26,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, between the dog running away
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:39.94,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,and someone's shoe going missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.94,0:14:42.44,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,nothing went according \Nto plan at this wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:45.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony was interrupted, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:53.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The key to solving this case \Nis that precise schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:02.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.36,0:15:06.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out. They're the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:12.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.53,0:15:16.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan wanted you \Nto look into something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.04,0:15:22.73,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, we've gathered the \Nwedding party as you requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.97,0:15:26.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? I never saidâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.70,0:15:29.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I must've said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.63,0:15:33.70,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:35.12,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.52,0:15:37.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The key element in this case
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.80,0:15:42.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,is the culprit's powerful thirst for revenge \Nagainst the victim Imamura Sayoko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:49.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A murder on the day of someone's \Nwedding is shocking enough on its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.25,0:15:54.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but the culprit intended to take her life \Nat the most dramatic moment possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.65,0:15:57.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,probably when the couple kissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:15:59.89,DCMain,NAHO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:02.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, they failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:06.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, the culprit had calculated \Nbackwards so that would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:08.82,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why they used \Nthe poisonous mushroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:09.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.81,0:16:13.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Consuming even a small amount \Nof the poisonous mushroom
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:16.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,used in this case causes \Ndeath within an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:18.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:24.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A fall from the height of happiness \Nis the perfect revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:28.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Kawasu Alex Harutoshi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.17,0:16:29.19,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.19,0:16:31.08,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,No way. The priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.77,0:16:36.18,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.36,0:16:40.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the only person who \Nknew about the Mativa chocolates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:44.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and could've swapped out their contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:51.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nobuteru-san learned the bride liked \Nchocolates during the wedding rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:54.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You were at the rehearsal \Nas well, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:58.57,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Nagashima-san the \Nwedding planner was there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:03.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nobuteru-san, when did you \Npurchase the chocolates?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:07.53,DCMain,NOBUTERU,0000,0000,0000,,I bought them today at a department \Nstore in Beika City before coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:08.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:13.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He knew the brand, but in order to \Npurchase the exact same chocolates,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:16.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he needed to see the moment you bought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:19.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So you followed Nobuteru-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.78,0:17:24.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After watching Nobuteru-san \Nbuy the chocolates,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:27.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you purchased the exact same product.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:32.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You poisoned the chocolates \Nusing the poison you brought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.16,0:17:36.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and waited for an opportunity to \Nswap yours with Nobuteru-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:42.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then you watched Nobuteru-san \Nfeed the chocolate to the bride
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:44.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and attended the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.90,0:17:46.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:48.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:49.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.35,0:17:50.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:52.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:55.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The wedding schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:17:57.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It really is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.72,0:18:00.16,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a precise schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.65,0:18:04.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The victim ate the chocolate at 12:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:08.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The groom lost his shoe and the \Nchihuahua interrupted the ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.51,0:18:10.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,delaying the schedule by roughly ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.15,0:18:15.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if you add ten \Nminutes to this schedule,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.14,0:18:18.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,one hour after when she consumed \Nthe poison at 13:45...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.89,0:18:20.95,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's when the couple kisses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.11,0:18:21.24,Kiss,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kiss
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.42,0:18:23.74,DCMain,HIROKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then the shoe was hidden by...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.03,0:18:28.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was also Kawasu-san who manipulated the \Nleash so the dog would interrupt the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:32.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By delaying the schedule \Na little bit at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.12,0:18:36.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he made it match up with when \Nthe bride would collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:40.26,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,And why would I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.69,0:18:43.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,At Mori-san's instruction, \NI looked into something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:46.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You apparently had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:49.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He attended the same \Nuniversity as Sayoko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.03,0:18:54.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but your \Nson was dating Sayoko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:57.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In his fourth year of university, \Nthey had a terrible breakup.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.53,0:19:01.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Several months later, he \Ndied in a traffic accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.09,0:19:04.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When you take into account the \Ntestimony concerning the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:08.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it's to easy imagine the difficult \Ntime your son must have had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:12.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's an adequate reason to seek revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:15.92,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,You even looked into that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.32,0:19:20.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I sensed the motive in this case \Nwas a powerful desire for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.12,0:19:29.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you're the only person \Nwho could have swapped the chocolates
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.00,0:19:30.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and could've seen Nakajima-san's schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.07,0:19:33.38,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.38,0:19:35.19,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:37.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.27,0:19:39.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You still have some chocolates, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:44.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to imagine someone like \Nyou would've thrown them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:51.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasu-san, you've hidden them in what you \Nbelieve to be the safest hiding place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.51,0:19:54.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're a clergyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:56.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You must've been supremely \Nconfident that your profession
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:00.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,would shield you from being searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.99,0:20:09.20,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,After toying with my son and \Ndriving him to his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.20,0:20:12.86,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,that woman didn't even come to his funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:21.36,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't allow that she-devil to happily \Nget married after the evil she committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.49,0:20:27.95,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I poisoned her so she'd die \Nduring her happiest moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.95,0:20:32.04,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,But she died before their kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.30,0:20:35.52,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,The poison was supposed to \Ntake effect after an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:40.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You said initially that it was too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:43.09,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,It's too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:45.23,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,She's too young.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.05,0:20:49.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You quickly added more to what you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:55.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but by "too soon," you meant \Nthat she collapsed too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:21:01.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When I realized what you meant,\NI became certain you were the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.01,0:21:08.80,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,I am amazed by how perceptive \Nyou are, Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:11.33,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,And thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.27,0:21:18.04,DCMain,ALEX,0000,0000,0000,,"Forgive us our sins, as we forgive \Nthose who sin against us."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.79,0:21:20.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.50,0:21:21.47,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Is he trying to kill himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.47,0:21:22.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.78,0:23:04.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Parents can't help\Nbut to care about their kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.86,0:23:11.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If Ran ever gets married...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.68,0:23:15.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll probably cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.63,0:23:18.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You would?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.42,0:23:26.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:32.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,While bawling my eyes out, I'll \Nbeat the groom into a bloody pulp!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.59,0:23:34.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Another beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.18,0:23:36.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.61,0:23:39.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm never letting you get married!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.72,0:23:44.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm never gonna be nobody's father-in-law!
